org.symphonyoss.client.services

Class ChatService

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.symphonyoss.client.services.ChatService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ChatListener

    public class ChatService
extends java.lang.Object
implements ChatListener
    The chat service provides capabilities to construct and monitor chat conversations. Supports the ability to add chat conversations which are validated and enriched. Supports the creation and callback of new chat conversations from incoming messages.

    NOTE: Multi-party conversations that are constructed via incoming messages are enriched over time. Currently there is no way of identifying all users of an incoming message from a given stream.

    • Method Detail

      • addChat

        public boolean addChat(Chat chat)
        Add a predefined chat to the service. RemoteUsers are required and streams will be generated and verified, so if one of the remote users are not connected to the BOT this will fail and return false.

        Note: In the future response object will be available to provide additional detail.

        Parameters:
        chat - Chat with remote users defined. Stream not required and will be generated.
        Returns:
        True if chat has been verified and accepted.
